channel.title: [urgent] !~read~! [urgent]
channel.description:
I have this weird bug i ran into this morning where my server cmd is online but its offline on status, my no-ip is up and running, and also when i try to login ill only be able to login when i just restart the server, now once im in-game if i logout i can't log back in 'error connection to server' this has never happend to me before and idk whats causing this. It's not my client and im using an allstar source I use the following ip's in my client example: *******.no-ip.biz, 127.0.0.1, 0.0.0.0, localhost non of them can connect back once your logged out it will say error connecting forever And the only thing i even touched was the server.java for a nullblocker i saw on forums.
And also i even tried running runserver.bat as admin and its the same. EDIT: IT DOES THIS TO ALL SERVERS
